                  <summary>
                     <p>I) ሰይፈ᎓ሥላሴ„Sword of the Trinity“ (fols. <locus from="5r" to="100r"/>)</p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#1"/>) Concluding prayer (fols. <locus from="5ra" to="14ra"/>), mistakenly copied as “Introduction” (marked with the word mäqdǝm in the top margin)</p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#2"/>) Reading for Monday (fols. <locus from="14r" to="26r"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#3"/>) Reading for Tuesday (fols. <locus from="26r" to="36v"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#4"/>) Reading for Wednesday (fols. <locus from="37r" to="48r"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#5"/>) Reading for Thursday (fols. <locus from="48v" to="61v"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#6"/>) Reading for Friday (fols. <locus from="61v" to="77v"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#7"/>) Reading for Saturday (fols. <locus from="77v" to="86v"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#8"/>) Reading for Sunday (fols. <locus from="86v" to="98r"/>) </p>
                     <p>I-<locus target="#9"/>) Reading for all days (fols. <locus from="98r" to="100r"/>)</p>
                     <!--Transcribed titles: I) Säyfäśǝllase-->
                     <!--Alternative titles: I) Zena nägäromulä-śǝllase“Story of the Matter of the Trinity”-->
                     <!--Author: The authorship of the Säyfäśǝllase is traditionally attributed to ˀabba Giyorgis of Gasǝa/Sägla (d. ca. 1425)-->
                  </summary>
